│ My search for `getConstant` in `LazyValueInfo.cpp` has been fruitful. The function `LazyValueInfo::getConstant` calls `getValueInBlock`, which seems to be the core of the analysis. I   │
│ also found a function `isKnownNonConstant` which explicitly checks for `AllocaInst` and returns `true`. This is the root of the problem.                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The function `isKnownNonConstant` prevents `LazyValueInfo` from ever trying to determine a constant value for an `alloca`. This is generally a safe assumption, as the address of an     │
│ alloca is not a constant. However, the *value stored in* an alloca can be constant. The current logic is too coarse and conflates the alloca itself with the values loaded from it.      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The miscompilation happens because a later pass asks for the value of a `load` from the alloca. `LazyValueInfo` should be able to determine this value. The current implementation seems │
│ to have a blind spot for this case.                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to make `isKnownNonConstant` less aggressive. It should not return `true` for an `AllocaInst`. By removing this check, `LazyValueInfo` will be allowed to analyze the value   │
│ of the alloca, trace its stores, and correctly determine the constant value loaded from it. This will prevent the incorrect deduction of undefined behavior.                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will now create a patch to comment out the `AllocaInst` check in the `isKnownNonConstant` function in `llvm/lib/Analysis/LazyValueInfo.cpp`.                                           │
