│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ I have successfully patched `LazyValueInfo.cpp` to remove the overly conservative check in `isKnownNonConstant` that prevented the analysis of `AllocaInst` values. This should allow    │
│ `LazyValueInfo` to correctly determine the value loaded from the alloca `%d` in the test case, even with the complex control flow created by `JumpThreading`. By correctly identifying   │
│ the loaded value as a constant, the optimizer will no longer be able to incorrectly deduce undefined behavior, thus fixing the miscompilation.                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This is a fundamental fix to the core value-tracking logic, and I am confident it is the correct solution. I will now run `submit-patch` to verify the fix.                              │
